ham, England":"英国達勒姆","durham county, england":"英国英格兰達勒姆達勒姆","lifeSummary":"当John Conyers于1323年之前出生在英国達勒姆索可本时，他的父亲Sir Roger Conyers42岁，母亲Alicia de Faye53岁。他于大约1369年与Lady Elizabeth Aton在英国達勒姆结婚。他们至少是2个儿子的父母。他去世于1395年。"},"hr":{"before 1323–1395":"prije 1323.–1395.","1296–Male":"1296–preminuo","1315–1396":"1315–1396","1323–1395":"1323.–1395.","1352–1419":"1352–1419","1376–Male":"1376–preminuo","1381–1431":"1381–1431","1280–1323":"1280–1323.","1270–1354":"1270–1354.","about 1381":"oko 1381.","before 1323":"prije 1323.","1352":"1352","1396":"1396","1395":"1395.","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1323":"1323.","1354":"1354.","about 1369":"oko 1369.","1453":"1453","1431":"1431","1376":"1376","about 1376":"oko 1376.","1419":"1419","1328":"1328","Sockburn,,Durham,England":"Sockburn, Durham, Engleska, United Kingdom","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England","durham county, england":"Durham, Durham, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"before 1323–1395":"před 1323–1395","1296–Male":"1296–Zesnulý","1315–1396":"1315–1396","1323–1395":"1323–1395","1352–1419":"1352–1419","1376–Male":"1376–Zesnulý","1381–1431":"1381–1431","1280–1323":"1280–1323","1270–1354":"1270–1354","about 1381":"okolo 1381","before 1323":"před 1323","1352":"1352","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1323":"1323","1354":"1354","about 1369":"okolo 1369","1453":"1453","1431":"1431","1376":"1376","about 1376":"okolo 1376","1419":"1419","1328":"1328","Sockburn,,Durham,England":"Sockburn, Durham, Anglie, United Kingdom","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, Anglie","Durham, England":"Durham, Anglie","durham county, england":"Durham, Durham, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"before 1323–1395":"før 1323–1395","1296–Male":"1296–Afdød","1315–1396":"1315–1396","1323–1395":"1323–1395","1352–1419":"1352–1419","1376–Male":"1376–Afdød","1381–1431":"1381–1431","1280–1323":"1280–1323","1270–1354":"1270–1354","about 1381":"omkring 1381","before 1323":"før 1323","1352":"1352","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1323":"1323","1354":"1354","about 1369":"omkring 1369","1453":"1453","1431":"1431","1376":"1376","about 1376":"omkring 1376","1419":"1419","1328":"1328","Sockburn,,Durham,England":"Sockburn, Durham, England, United Kingdom","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England","durham county, england":"Durham, Durham, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"before 1323–1395":"vóór 1323–1395","1296–Male":"1296–Overleden","1315–1396":"1315–1396","1323–1395":"1323–1395","1352–1419":"1352–1419","1376–Male":"1376–Overleden","1381–1431":"1381–1431","1280–1323":"1280–1323","1270–1354":"1270–1354","about 1381":"circa 1381","before 1323":"vóór 1323","1352":"1352","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1323":"1323","1354":"1354","about 1369":"circa 1369","1453":"1453","1431":"1431","1376":"1376","about 1376":"circa 1376","1419":"1419","1328":"1328","Sockburn,,Durham,England":"Sockburn, Durham, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England","durham county, england":"Durham, Durham, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"before 1323–1395":"before 1323–1395","1296–Male":"1296–Deceased","1315–1396":"1315–1396","1323–1395":"1323–1395","1352–1419":"1352–1419","1376–Male":"1376–Deceased","1381–1431":"1381–1431","1280–1323":"1280–1323","1270–1354":"1270–1354","about 1381":"about 1381","before 1323":"before 1323","1352":"1352","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1323":"1323","1354":"1354","about 1369":"about 1369","1453":"1453","1431":"1431","1376":"1376","about 1376":"about 1376","1419":"1419","1328":"1328","Sockburn,,Durham,England":"Sockburn, Durham, England, United Kingdom","Sockburn, Durham, England":"Sockburn, Durham, England","Durham, England":"Durham, England","durham county, england":"Durham, Durham, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Conyers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire, of Norman origin): habitational name from either of two places in northern France, Coignières in Seine-et-Oise or Cogners in Sarthe. Alternatively, a variant of   Conyer  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Conyer","meanings":["English: occupational name for a minter, a coiner of money, from an agent derivative of Old French <i>coignier</i> ‘to stamp money, to mint’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":5,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":14,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":59,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Conyers was born before 1323, in Sockburn, Durham, England, his father, Sir Roger Conyers, was 42 and his mother, Alicia de Faye, was 53. He married Lady Elizabeth Aton about 1369, in Durham, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1395."},"et":{"before 1323–1395":"enne 1323–1395","1296–Male":"1296–Surnud","1315–1396":"1315–1396","1323–1395":"1323–1395","1352–1419":"1352–1419","1376–Male":"1376–Surnud","1381–1431":"1381–1431","1280–